        <briefdescription>
<para>Constructor for the <ref refid="classJSL_1_1Log_1_1Core" kindref="compound">Core</ref>, initialises an entry in the output log. Should never be called outside <ref refid="Core_8h_1aba7b09d6e8fbe414c23705ad24dde6ff" kindref="member">LOG</ref>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Note that the Level is used purely for formatting purposes: a <ref refid="classJSL_1_1Log_1_1Core" kindref="compound">Core</ref> object <emphasis>always</emphasis> outputs a stream. The <lsquo/>log suppression checks<rsquo/> are performed by <ref refid="Core_8h_1aba7b09d6e8fbe414c23705ad24dde6ff" kindref="member">LOG</ref>. The three &apos;calling&apos; parameters are used to locate the origin of a LOG; they are provided by compile-time flags, but are only used by ERROR and WARN output.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>level</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The LogLevel that the associated entry will be on. Determines formatting. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>callingLine</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>This is the ƒile line on which the <ref refid="Core_8h_1aba7b09d6e8fbe414c23705ad24dde6ff" kindref="member">LOG</ref> call appears </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>callingFunction</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The function in which the LOG call occurred. Provides a pseudo-stack-unwinding. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>callingFile</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The file in which the callingFunction is found. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
